            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="619" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d619">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.CC/6–245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="48" xml:id="d619fn48">Secretary of State Stettinius was attending the
                        United Nations Conference at San Francisco.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-02">June 2,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. It was my understanding that the following telegram had been sent by the
                    President to you directly on May 30:</p>
                <p>“Please inform Soong orally that Marshal Stalin desires to discuss important
                    matters with him in Moscow not later than July first.</p>
                <pb facs="0902" n="892" xml:id="pg_892"/>
                <p>“We will provide air transportation to Moscow upon receipt of advance information
                    of the date of his departure.</p>
                <p>“For your information this proposed meeting is for a discussion of the tripartite
                    agreement reached at Yalta in regard to Japan.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
